## 2026-04-05 - No lightweight "find references" for tokens
- Added inline "Find references" feature to token list rows. Clicking the chain-link icon button in the hover actions toolbar (or selecting "Find references" from the right-click context menu) opens a popover listing all tokens in the current flat token map that alias the hovered token via `{path}` syntax.
- Popover shows token count in header, each referencing token as a clickable row (clicking navigates to it via `onNavigateToAlias`), and a set-name badge when the referencing token lives in a different set. Dismisses on click-outside or Escape.
- Computation is fully client-side using the `allTokensFlat` already available in context — no API call needed. Module-level `hasDirectRef` + `getIncomingRefs` helpers handle simple string aliases as well as composite token values (shadow, border, typography, etc.) with nested sub-properties.

